Amazon redshift and Google bigquery require SQL queries to pull data

SQL is out for 50 years almost and is still relevant in almost any industry 

Attribute (column)
Tuple(row)


SQL is not a general-purpose programming language.
It is a special-purpose programming language 
The kind of programming is called declarative which is different than like python (imperative programming)

Anyway there are extension that allow SQL to do more like 
Oracle that has procedural language (PL-SQL)
And SQL Server that has transact SQL 

You can do more with these

ANSI SQLrefers to SQL code that follows the ANSI standard 

Try to use the latest standard also for compatibility between RDBMS 
Anyways have a look to older standards as it has probably been used by your company years ago
